.TH SP_IS_DEBUG 3 DATE "libstaple-VERSION"
.SH NAME
sp_is_debug \- check if the library has been compiled with debug mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.ad l
#include <staple.h>
.sp
int
.BR sp_is_debug (void)
.sp
Link with \fI-lstaple\fP.
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR sp_is_debug ()
function can be used at runtime to determine whether the staple library has been
compiled with debug mode or not.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR sp_is_debug ()
function shall return 1 if debug mode is active and 0 otherwise.
.SH ERRORS
.P
The
.BR sp_is_debug ()
function shall never fail.
.SH CONFORMING TO
See
.BR libstaple (7).
.SH SEE ALSO
.ad l
.BR libstaple (7)
